wikipedia_page.main: Albert William "Jock" Stallard, Baron Stallard (5 November 1921 – 29 March 2008) was a British Labour politician.  He served as a councillor in St Pancras and Camden, and then as a Member of Parliament (MP).  He retired from the House of Commons at the 1983 general election and became a life peer in the 1983 Dissolution Honours.
